On September 15, 2023, Vice President Kamala Harris visited North Carolina A&T University as part of her College Tour. She emphasized the importance of young leaders and their role in shaping the future of the country. Harris also discussed the significance of voting and highlighted the impact of young voters in the 2020 election. She addressed the issue of gun violence and called for measures such as an assault weapons ban and universal background checks. The Vice President also spoke about reproductive rights and the need to protect women's autonomy over their bodies. Additionally, Harris and Administrator Michael Regan discussed environmental justice and the administration's efforts to combat environmental racism. They emphasized the importance of diversity, equity, and inclusion in addressing climate change and other issues. The discussion concluded with Harris encouraging the students to stay optimistic and reminding them that they are not alone in their journey.